1
00:00:01,200 --> 00:00:02,200
All this?

2
00:00:02,310 --> 00:00:04,080
Can I really take whatever I like?

3
00:00:05,210 --> 00:00:06,210
Of course.

4
00:00:07,200 --> 00:00:09,560
Knowing these were part of
Kuji Yoshiharu-san's collection,

5
00:00:09,920 --> 00:00:12,070
I just want to take them all.

6
00:00:13,060 --> 00:00:14,060
Don't be ridiculous.

7
00:00:14,740 --> 00:00:17,169
Ever since I was in college,

8
00:00:17,170 --> 00:00:19,270
Kuji-san has always looked after me.

9
00:00:20,270 --> 00:00:21,896
The reason I joined the
publishing house in the first place

10
00:00:21,920 --> 00:00:24,750
was because I was
determined to work with him.

11
00:00:27,580 --> 00:00:29,759
Nice, oden!

12
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:31,749
Go wash your hands.

13
00:00:31,750 --> 00:00:32,750
Alright.

14
00:00:34,230 --> 00:00:36,260
Hey, what's this?

15
00:00:37,710 --> 00:00:40,630
Your mom sent it to me.

16
00:00:40,930 --> 00:00:41,930
Whoa.

17
00:00:41,980 --> 00:00:45,560
Two grown men, how are we
supposed to finish a box this big?

18
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:46,900
Still, I'm grateful.

19
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:48,300
Yeah.

20
00:00:48,483 --> 00:00:51,063
She's always been like this.

21
00:00:52,830 --> 00:00:55,150
I understand she wants
to show her appreciation,

22
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:57,470
but if she just thought
about it for a second,

23
00:00:57,750 --> 00:00:59,590
she'd realize it's
actually a bit of a burden.

24
00:01:01,350 --> 00:01:02,350
Ah...

25
00:01:02,950 --> 00:01:05,010
This will probably keep
happening, won't it?

26
00:01:10,440 --> 00:01:11,440
No.

27
00:01:11,546 --> 00:01:16,286
Maybe the problem is that I've
never addressed this disconnect.

28
00:01:17,930 --> 00:01:18,930
I get it.

29
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:22,519
When I lived with my father,

30
00:01:22,520 --> 00:01:24,190
I was constantly frustrated too.

31
00:01:25,110 --> 00:01:26,540
Your father was like that too?

32
00:01:27,110 --> 00:01:28,110
Yeah.

33
00:01:29,170 --> 00:01:30,870
I'd often vent to Sawada-san and

34
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:33,100
Mikami-san, our housekeeper,

35
00:01:33,620 --> 00:01:35,080
in the kitchen.

36
00:01:35,590 --> 00:01:37,030
Oh, you had a housekeeper?

37
00:01:37,420 --> 00:01:38,420
Yeah.

38
00:01:38,470 --> 00:01:39,750
After my mother passed away.

39
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:42,360
Ah.

40
00:01:43,960 --> 00:01:46,040
I just remembered Mikami-san loves apples.

41
00:01:46,820 --> 00:01:48,020
Can I take a few for her?

42
00:01:48,630 --> 00:01:49,630
Of course.

43
00:01:50,610 --> 00:01:53,040
It's hard to find an excuse
to see her otherwise.

44
00:01:53,370 --> 00:01:54,370
You're a lifesaver.

45
00:02:03,340 --> 00:02:04,880
Delicious.

46
00:02:42,700 --> 00:02:48,100
"Life In Smokey Blue"

47
00:02:48,450 --> 00:02:50,980
(Episode 6: Learning to Let Go)
Those apples look so good.

48
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:52,580
I'm so happy.

49
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:55,700
I'm sorry to have made
you come all this way.

50
00:02:55,730 --> 00:02:58,990
Not at all, I insisted on coming.

51
00:02:59,570 --> 00:03:00,670
How have you been?

52
00:03:01,710 --> 00:03:04,050
Can't complain, I'm getting by.

53
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,560
Here you go.

54
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:07,800
Thank you.

55
00:03:14,540 --> 00:03:15,880
This is good.

56
00:03:18,090 --> 00:03:20,500
I haven't seen you at the
Komaba supermarket lately.

57
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:22,360
I was wondering if something happened.

58
00:03:22,710 --> 00:03:24,090
The Komaba supermarket?

59
00:03:24,280 --> 00:03:28,020
Didn't they switch to
self-checkout last year?

60
00:03:28,560 --> 00:03:29,980
I'm not very good with those.

61
00:03:30,160 --> 00:03:31,160
Ah...

62
00:03:31,490 --> 00:03:32,570
The self-checkout machines.

63
00:03:35,835 --> 00:03:39,145
By the way, Minoru-san is
finally coming back to Japan, right?

64
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:40,719
The last time he was here,

65
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:42,210
he stopped by my place.

66
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:45,470
Eno-chan has grown so much.

67
00:03:45,670 --> 00:03:46,730
She has.

68
00:03:47,400 --> 00:03:50,450
Minoru-san is going to be
living in this house now, right?

69
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:52,660
So, where will Kuji-san be moving to?

70
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:57,470
I'm still looking.

71
00:04:02,900 --> 00:04:05,520
I used to stew apples often too.

72
00:04:06,210 --> 00:04:08,530
And banana cake.

73
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:13,030
You and Minoru-san both loved it.

74
00:04:13,720 --> 00:04:14,870
Oh, right.

75
00:04:15,410 --> 00:04:18,410
I found this while
cleaning up the other day.

76
00:04:20,320 --> 00:04:22,280
I really wanted to show you.

77
00:04:29,380 --> 00:04:30,580
Banana cake.

78
00:04:31,180 --> 00:04:32,380
I really loved that back then.

79
00:04:33,340 --> 00:04:34,340
So,

80
00:04:34,510 --> 00:04:35,510
Azuma-kun,

81
00:04:35,802 --> 00:04:39,220
why did you translate the
protagonist as 'Mr. Rabbit'

82
00:04:39,460 --> 00:04:40,880
instead of just 'Rabbit'?

83
00:04:41,590 --> 00:04:42,790
Uh...

84
00:04:44,810 --> 00:04:46,010
I just felt

85
00:04:46,260 --> 00:04:49,290
it sounded a bit more whimsical.

86
00:04:49,790 --> 00:04:50,810
Whimsical?

87
00:04:51,460 --> 00:04:52,460
Yes.

88
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:54,760
Hmm...

89
00:04:56,920 --> 00:04:58,180
Whimsical, huh...

90
00:05:01,020 --> 00:05:03,310
I hadn't thought of it that way,

91
00:05:03,860 --> 00:05:05,470
but 'Mr. Rabbit'

92
00:05:05,650 --> 00:05:09,210
does have that Aesop's Fables feel to it.

93
00:05:10,990 --> 00:05:12,880
I see.

94
00:05:16,937 --> 00:05:17,937
Wait?

95
00:05:18,151 --> 00:05:20,071
You took a highway bus
all the way from Sendai?!

96
00:05:20,390 --> 00:05:21,390
Yes.

97
00:05:21,910 --> 00:05:25,300
And then another hour
drive from Sendai Station.

98
00:05:26,230 --> 00:05:28,200
That must have been exhausting.

99
00:05:32,500 --> 00:05:33,500
Hara-san,

100
00:05:33,940 --> 00:05:36,100
what made you decide to
start studying at this school?

101
00:05:39,030 --> 00:05:42,570
When I was younger, I studied
hard to become a translator,

102
00:05:42,990 --> 00:05:44,960
but I gave it up when I
got married and pregnant.

103
00:05:47,770 --> 00:05:50,010
Though I ended up getting divorced anyway.

104
00:05:51,550 --> 00:05:52,550
I see.

105
00:05:54,160 --> 00:05:57,030
I worked myself to the
bone raising my child alone,

106
00:05:58,300 --> 00:06:00,570
but once they were grown and independent,

107
00:06:01,430 --> 00:06:03,050
a thought suddenly struck me.

108
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:07,770
I felt envious of friends who
had achieved their dreams,

109
00:06:09,250 --> 00:06:11,620
like I was the only one left behind.

110
00:06:12,570 --> 00:06:13,860
That's how it felt.

111
00:06:15,570 --> 00:06:16,570
Ah.

112
00:06:18,060 --> 00:06:19,060
I understand.

113
00:06:20,190 --> 00:06:22,310
So at fifty, I decided
to give it another shot.

114
00:06:22,810 --> 00:06:24,610
It was mostly just a whim,

115
00:06:26,070 --> 00:06:28,480
but sometimes a whim is all you need.

116
00:06:29,060 --> 00:06:30,160
That's true.

117
00:06:34,860 --> 00:06:36,070
I'm home.

118
00:06:44,730 --> 00:06:46,250
What are you cooking? It smells great.

119
00:06:46,840 --> 00:06:48,650
Candied apples and sweet potatoes.

120
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:50,890
Mikami-san taught me how to make it.

121
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:55,160
Here.

122
00:06:58,360 --> 00:06:59,410
It's hot!

123
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:01,420
It's good.

124
00:07:04,810 --> 00:07:06,110
How's the house hunt going?

125
00:07:08,410 --> 00:07:09,410
Eh.

126
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:10,680
It's going.

127
00:07:13,890 --> 00:07:15,789
When you said you were moving in,

128
00:07:15,790 --> 00:07:17,490
didn't I tell you?

129
00:07:17,890 --> 00:07:19,850
I'm moving out.

130
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:22,810
This house was inherited by my brother.

131
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:25,160
I know, I know...

132
00:07:35,490 --> 00:07:37,290
Is that homework for
your translation school?

133
00:07:37,340 --> 00:07:39,750
Yeah, I'm stuck on this part.

134
00:07:39,780 --> 00:07:41,370
Hey, can I take a look?

135
00:07:44,430 --> 00:07:45,430
Right here.

136
00:07:45,670 --> 00:07:47,486
I'm debating whether to
just use the word 'Lemmings'

137
00:07:47,510 --> 00:07:50,060
or translate it as 'Tabinezumi'.

138
00:07:50,460 --> 00:07:53,000
Why not just use 'Lemmings'?

139
00:07:53,420 --> 00:07:54,630
It's fine I guess,

140
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:56,839
but considering the target
age group for this book,

141
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:58,306
I'm worried it might be
too hard to understand.

142
00:07:58,330 --> 00:07:59,330
Ah.

143
00:07:59,470 --> 00:08:00,570
I see.

144
00:08:01,070 --> 00:08:03,040
You have to think
about things like that too?

145
00:08:03,390 --> 00:08:04,390
Yeah.

146
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:07,440
Doing homework at my age.

147
00:08:09,010 --> 00:08:10,249
I never thought that at this age,

148
00:08:10,250 --> 00:08:12,110
I'd be chasing a dream.

149
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:17,230
I think that's amazing.

150
00:08:19,260 --> 00:08:20,260
Huh?

151
00:08:20,850 --> 00:08:22,000
It really is.

152
00:08:22,570 --> 00:08:27,840
I've always admired how
straightforward you are, Azuma-kun.

153
00:08:32,550 --> 00:08:34,390
Ah, Tajimi-san.

154
00:08:34,530 --> 00:08:35,890
Aren't you going to eat something?

155
00:08:36,820 --> 00:08:37,990
Ah...

156
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:41,100
Ah... You're right. I'll
go pick something up.

157
00:08:41,210 --> 00:08:42,210
Yeah.

158
00:08:43,170 --> 00:08:44,930
- Good luck.
- Thanks.

159
00:08:48,170 --> 00:08:49,700
It's about to give out.

160
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:51,240
The damage is pretty severe.

161
00:08:51,380 --> 00:08:52,380
Yeah.

162
00:08:52,510 --> 00:08:54,800
The floor around here
doesn't look too good either.

163
00:08:56,530 --> 00:08:57,530
Oh?

164
00:08:58,140 --> 00:08:59,270
An old dictionary.

165
00:09:01,710 --> 00:09:03,776
That's the English-Japanese
dictionary my father used.

166
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:05,290
Oh.

167
00:09:10,670 --> 00:09:11,770
It has a lot of character.

168
00:09:12,990 --> 00:09:13,990
Yeah, it really does.

169
00:09:16,450 --> 00:09:18,230
Is this going to get recycled?

170
00:09:18,660 --> 00:09:19,960
Huh? Why?

171
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:23,400
It's so old, you're not
going to use it anyway.

172
00:09:25,540 --> 00:09:27,090
Can I have it then?

173
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:29,840
I don't mind.

174
00:09:30,750 --> 00:09:31,750
Great.

175
00:09:38,910 --> 00:09:41,140
Minoru-senpai, where to next?

176
00:09:41,420 --> 00:09:44,539
Ah, could you take the
desk on the second floor?

177
00:09:44,540 --> 00:09:45,140
Got it.

178
00:09:45,230 --> 00:09:47,090
- It's heavy.
- No problem, leave it to me.

179
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:50,030
What an impressive human chain.

180
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:52,360
As expected.

181
00:09:53,340 --> 00:09:55,540
It's better to get it all done at once.

182
00:09:56,560 --> 00:09:58,310
That way, you don't get too sentimental.

183
00:10:04,890 --> 00:10:06,090
I guess so...

184
00:10:07,160 --> 00:10:09,890
- See you.
- Thanks, good work today.

185
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:15,670
I'm glad we finished before dark.

186
00:10:17,290 --> 00:10:18,290
Yeah.

187
00:10:21,430 --> 00:10:24,030
I'm heading back to the hotel.

188
00:10:25,150 --> 00:10:26,150
Yeah.

189
00:10:30,870 --> 00:10:32,400
Mikami-san.

190
00:10:32,940 --> 00:10:36,550
I heard you were back,
and I just had to see you.

191
00:10:36,950 --> 00:10:39,059
- Please, come in.
- No, that's alright.

192
00:10:39,060 --> 00:10:41,280
I'll just drop this off and be on my way.

193
00:10:43,180 --> 00:10:44,750
It's banana cake.

194
00:10:45,380 --> 00:10:46,900
Thank you so much.

195
00:10:50,010 --> 00:10:51,980
- Is something wrong?
- Oh, I'm sorry.

196
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:54,819
Seeing the two of you together like this,

197
00:10:54,820 --> 00:10:56,160
it just makes me so happy.

198
00:10:59,730 --> 00:11:00,730
Yeah.

199
00:11:01,860 --> 00:11:05,670
Mikami-san probably didn't
expect us to wolf it down like that.

200
00:11:08,220 --> 00:11:09,420
True.

201
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:13,630
So good.

202
00:11:15,010 --> 00:11:16,010
Ah.

203
00:11:16,990 --> 00:11:17,990
Delicious.

204
00:11:19,530 --> 00:11:20,530
Hey, do you remember?

205
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:23,150
The first time Mikami-san

206
00:11:23,520 --> 00:11:25,210
made us banana bread?

207
00:11:27,280 --> 00:11:28,480
She put raisins in it.

208
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:34,620
I really can't stand raisins.

209
00:11:36,680 --> 00:11:38,080
But I was just a kid then,

210
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,550
so I couldn't tell her to her face.

211
00:11:43,950 --> 00:11:44,950
And then,

212
00:11:46,200 --> 00:11:47,440
you secretly

213
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:49,560
ate all the raisins out of my portion.

214
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:52,790
Yeah, that happened.

215
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,400
Later, you even politely told Mikami-san

216
00:11:57,290 --> 00:12:01,800
that we weren't really fans of raisins.

217
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:04,760
I remember thinking back then,

218
00:12:06,350 --> 00:12:08,370
my brother is so mature.

219
00:12:09,530 --> 00:12:10,730
I really looked up to you.

220
00:12:12,940 --> 00:12:14,190
You're exaggerating.

221
00:12:20,650 --> 00:12:21,650
There was that one time,

222
00:12:23,673 --> 00:12:25,513
we asked Mikami-san for the recipe

223
00:12:26,540 --> 00:12:28,480
and we made the banana
bread together, right?

224
00:12:29,910 --> 00:12:30,910
Ah.

225
00:12:31,600 --> 00:12:32,600
Yeah, that's right.

226
00:12:33,060 --> 00:12:34,060
Back then,

227
00:12:34,810 --> 00:12:36,400
I even took some to my father.

228
00:12:38,380 --> 00:12:39,380
But,

229
00:12:40,460 --> 00:12:41,770
he wouldn't even look at it,

230
00:12:42,750 --> 00:12:44,830
just said he doesn't eat sweets.

231
00:12:47,870 --> 00:12:48,870
I see...

232
00:12:51,610 --> 00:12:53,820
Even though I knew
exactly what he was like,

233
00:12:55,850 --> 00:12:57,370
I kept hoping for something different,

234
00:12:58,030 --> 00:12:59,230
only to be disappointed again.

235
00:13:02,630 --> 00:13:03,630
But,

236
00:13:04,250 --> 00:13:05,670
that junior who came by today,

237
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:09,190
he was so happy to finally
pay off his student loans.

238
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:13,240
As for me,

239
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,580
I never had to go through that struggle.

240
00:13:18,200 --> 00:13:19,560
I sailed through my student years.

241
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:23,720
I'm grateful to him just for that.

242
00:13:25,420 --> 00:13:27,380
And I truly respect him for his work.

243
00:13:29,830 --> 00:13:31,110
I've resented him,

244
00:13:32,810 --> 00:13:34,010
and I've even hated him.

245
00:13:37,170 --> 00:13:38,170
But...

246
00:13:41,830 --> 00:13:43,030
I'm also grateful to him.

247
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:47,360
Shizuka.

248
00:13:50,250 --> 00:13:54,090
I'm going to build a great house.

249
00:14:02,920 --> 00:14:03,920
Yeah.

250
00:14:41,910 --> 00:14:45,710
Is there anything you hate to eat?

251
00:14:49,340 --> 00:14:50,340
Raisins.

252
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:54,910
If it's raisins,

253
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:57,800
I won't use them.

254
00:14:59,140 --> 00:15:00,880
So you really hate raisins, huh?

255
00:15:02,170 --> 00:15:03,170
Yeah.

256
00:15:03,420 --> 00:15:04,420
I really do.

257
00:15:06,330 --> 00:15:07,730
Even though I'd forgotten about it.

258
00:15:09,870 --> 00:15:11,130
What the hell...

259
00:15:22,460 --> 00:15:23,460
Ah.

260
00:15:23,810 --> 00:15:25,610
You kept the sofa.

261
00:15:26,950 --> 00:15:28,610
I figured I'd keep it a while longer.

262
00:15:29,110 --> 00:15:30,310
It was expensive, after all.

263
00:15:30,550 --> 00:15:31,630
And it's Chippendale style.

264
00:15:31,920 --> 00:15:32,920
Wait.

265
00:15:33,030 --> 00:15:34,030
For real?

266
00:15:36,870 --> 00:15:38,250
- Just kidding.
- You jerk.

267
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:49,810
I just had a dream.

268
00:15:50,690 --> 00:15:51,690
A dream?

269
00:15:52,620 --> 00:15:53,620
What kind of dream?

270
00:15:56,430 --> 00:15:57,810
The people who used to be busy

271
00:15:58,059 --> 00:15:59,459
in the kitchen of this house.

272
00:16:00,650 --> 00:16:01,650
My mother,

273
00:16:01,740 --> 00:16:02,740
and Mikami-san.

274
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:08,440
This house,

275
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:12,850
was built by my grandfather's generation.

276
00:16:14,910 --> 00:16:17,080
Through constant renovations and care,

277
00:16:18,380 --> 00:16:20,140
it's been passed down
for three generations.

278
00:16:24,910 --> 00:16:27,930
Your mom and grandma,

279
00:16:28,410 --> 00:16:29,410
Mikami-san,

280
00:16:30,310 --> 00:16:31,750
you and your brother.

281
00:16:34,430 --> 00:16:36,720
Thinking that I, too,
once stood in this kitchen,

282
00:16:39,510 --> 00:16:41,790
and was part of this house's history,

283
00:16:43,220 --> 00:16:44,320
I feel honored.

284
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:56,600
Yesterday,

285
00:16:57,190 --> 00:16:59,060
I signed a lease for a new apartment.

286
00:16:59,110 --> 00:17:00,319
Yeah, me too.
I found one in Nakano...

287
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:02,649
This house is going to be torn down.

288
00:17:02,650 --> 00:17:04,120
They're going to build a new one.

289
00:17:09,330 --> 00:17:10,330
Huh?

290
00:17:14,220 --> 00:17:17,570
My brother is building a new house.

291
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:22,300
Torn down?

292
00:17:23,470 --> 00:17:24,570
This house?

293
00:17:25,020 --> 00:17:26,020
Yeah.

294
00:17:26,270 --> 00:17:27,100
Why?

295
00:17:27,101 --> 00:17:28,576
Didn't your brother say
he was going to live here?

296
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:29,709
I never heard anything
about tearing it down.

297
00:17:29,710 --> 00:17:30,970
It's already been decided.

298
00:17:40,060 --> 00:17:42,020
It's time to say goodbye to this house.

299
00:17:48,420 --> 00:17:49,660
You've done well.

300
00:17:50,120 --> 00:17:50,630
Huh?

301
00:17:50,631 --> 00:17:51,980
Isn't today the day you're moving?

302
00:17:51,990 --> 00:17:52,996
Didn't you take the day off?

303
00:17:53,020 --> 00:17:54,330
I don't have much to pack.

304
00:17:54,570 --> 00:17:55,770
Wow, that's a surprise.

305
00:17:56,330 --> 00:17:58,730
Your apartment was always
packed with stuff back in college.

306
00:17:58,800 --> 00:17:59,800
True.

307
00:18:00,170 --> 00:18:01,170
You two,

308
00:18:01,520 --> 00:18:04,500
you were seniors and
juniors in college, right?

309
00:18:04,770 --> 00:18:05,770
Yeah.

310
00:18:06,090 --> 00:18:08,050
Though that was almost 20 years ago.

311
00:18:08,500 --> 00:18:09,730
It's hard to imagine

312
00:18:10,400 --> 00:18:12,050
that you two were once college students.

313
00:18:13,283 --> 00:18:15,503
It feels like yesterday to me, too,

314
00:18:15,770 --> 00:18:18,010
but at the same time, it
feels like a hundred years ago.

315
00:18:18,510 --> 00:18:20,610
Before I knew it, I was an adult.

316
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:23,760
I don't know what you're talking about.

317
00:18:25,170 --> 00:18:27,190
Even though we're adults now,

318
00:18:28,230 --> 00:18:32,440
it feels like we're just pretending to be.

319
00:19:01,620 --> 00:19:03,110
Back to that house.

320
00:19:05,340 --> 00:19:06,540
Today is the last time.

321
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:17,330
Look at you, you're
too old to be this drunk.

322
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:22,760
Get up, we're going home.

323
00:19:23,810 --> 00:19:24,810
What a pain.

324
00:19:25,380 --> 00:19:26,380
Huh?

325
00:19:27,260 --> 00:19:29,850
It's too much trouble to stand up and walk.

326
00:19:35,730 --> 00:19:36,730
Yeah.

327
00:19:38,170 --> 00:19:39,370
Give me a piggyback ride.

328
00:19:43,450 --> 00:19:44,920
Just so you know,

329
00:19:46,250 --> 00:19:48,740
you're not cute at all like this.

330
00:19:49,740 --> 00:19:52,810
Alright, hop on. Heave-ho.

331
00:19:56,350 --> 00:19:57,350
Amazing.

332
00:19:57,990 --> 00:19:59,550
I'm getting a
piggyback ride from Kuji.

333
00:20:00,940 --> 00:20:02,510
Quiet down, you drunkard.

334
00:20:04,540 --> 00:20:05,540
Shut up.

335
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:09,700
Kuji.

336
00:20:10,460 --> 00:20:11,790
You know,

337
00:20:12,770 --> 00:20:14,990
I really love that house.

338
00:20:15,650 --> 00:20:16,650
It's old,

339
00:20:17,080 --> 00:20:18,390
beautiful,

340
00:20:19,350 --> 00:20:21,340
freezing in the winter,

341
00:20:22,050 --> 00:20:24,310
but the garden is beautiful in the spring.

342
00:20:25,790 --> 00:20:27,590
It's boiling in the summer,

343
00:20:28,740 --> 00:20:30,860
and the garden grows like a jungle.

344
00:20:32,530 --> 00:20:33,530
Yeah.

345
00:20:36,080 --> 00:20:37,080
Yeah.

346
00:20:37,910 --> 00:20:39,530
In your hair,

347
00:20:40,770 --> 00:20:42,210
I can smell the scent of your house.

348
00:20:42,923 --> 00:20:44,433
And the smell of an old man.

349
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:47,060
Shut up.

350
00:20:47,450 --> 00:20:48,550
You're the same way.

351
00:20:49,880 --> 00:20:51,400
One day, this old man will

352
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:54,990
become an even older man.

353
00:21:00,180 --> 00:21:01,180
Kuji.

354
00:21:02,730 --> 00:21:03,730
I thought

355
00:21:04,960 --> 00:21:06,280
you'd live in that house forever.

356
00:21:07,140 --> 00:21:09,510
Become an old man,

357
00:21:11,060 --> 00:21:13,410
in that house you're so used to,

358
00:21:13,780 --> 00:21:16,210
eating in that kitchen,

359
00:21:16,950 --> 00:21:18,580
looking out at the garden,

360
00:21:20,510 --> 00:21:24,730
and finally passing away
peacefully on that veranda.

361
00:21:25,690 --> 00:21:26,990
That's what I always thought...

362
00:21:30,730 --> 00:21:32,990
Don't decide where I'm going to die.

363
00:21:35,710 --> 00:21:36,710
Kuji.

364
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:40,800
You've worked so hard.

365
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:43,680
For your family,

366
00:21:45,820 --> 00:21:47,310
for this house.

367
00:21:48,810 --> 00:21:50,240
You've really done your best.

368
00:21:54,390 --> 00:21:55,490
You're amazing.

369
00:21:58,520 --> 00:21:59,650
You've done well.

370
00:22:00,310 --> 00:22:01,310
Kuji.

371
00:22:03,960 --> 00:22:05,160
That house,

372
00:22:08,130 --> 00:22:09,230
it really suits you.

373
00:22:09,410 --> 00:22:10,940
It really does.

374
00:22:13,090 --> 00:22:14,090
Is that so?

375
00:22:19,650 --> 00:22:21,720
I wish that were true.

376
00:22:28,450 --> 00:22:30,070
It rained the next day.

377
00:22:32,560 --> 00:22:33,660
Hungover,

378
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:35,690
I stumbled out the door.

379
00:22:49,180 --> 00:22:51,000
I heard that after that,

380
00:22:52,270 --> 00:22:54,040
Kuji stayed in that house for another week.

381
00:23:00,560 --> 00:23:02,656
(Next Episode)
Since Tajimi-san is in the hospital,

382
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:04,200
I bought something for the first time.

383
00:23:04,360 --> 00:23:06,800
I wanted to give it to Tajimi-san.

384
00:23:07,210 --> 00:23:08,230
That was actually

385
00:23:08,530 --> 00:23:09,860
a white lie.

386
00:23:10,150 --> 00:23:11,150
In reality,

387
00:23:12,020 --> 00:23:14,390
I just wanted to make myself feel better.
